The '''1971 Monte Carlo Open''' was a combined men's and women's [[tennis]] tournament played on [[Clay court|outdoor clay courts]] at the [[Monte Carlo Country Club]] in [[Monte Carlo]], [[Monaco]] . The men's tournament was part of the [[1971 Grand Prix (tennis)|1971 Pepsi-Cola Grand Prix]] circuit. It was the 65th edition of the event and was held from 5 April through 11 April 1971. [[Ilie Năstase]] and [[Gail Chanfreau]] won the singles titles.
==Champions== ===Men's Singles=== {{flagicon|ROU|1965}} '''[[Ilie Năstase]]''' defeated {{flagicon|NED}} [[Tom Okker]] 3–6, 8–6, 6–1, 6–1
===Women's Singles=== {{flagicon|FRA}} '''[[Gail Chanfreau]]''' defeated {{flagicon|NED}} [[Betty Stöve]] 6–4, 4–6, 6–4
===Men's Doubles=== {{flagicon|ROU|1965}} '''[[Ilie Năstase]]''' / {{flagicon|ROU|1965}} '''[[Ion Țiriac]]''' defeated {{flagicon|NED}} [[Tom Okker]] / {{flagicon|GBR}} [[Roger Taylor (tennis)|Roger Taylor]] 1–6, 6–3, 6–3, 8–6
===Women's Doubles=== {{flagicon|FRG}} '''[[Katja Ebbinghaus]]''' / {{flagicon|NED}} '''[[Betty Stöve]]''' defeated {{flagicon|ITA}} [[Lucia Bassi]] / {{flagicon|ITA}} [[Lea Pericoli]] 6–4, 6–3
