'''Ashongman''' is a developing town in the [[Ga East Municipal District|Ga East Municipal district]], a [[Districts of Ghana|district]] in the [[Greater Accra Region]] of [[Ghana]].<ref name="Ga East Municipal District">[http://gaeast.ghanadistricts.gov.gh/?arrow=dnf&_=2&r=1&rlv=towns Ga East Municipal District]</ref>
==Town structure== The town is under the jurisdiction of the [[Ga East Municipal District]] and is in the [[Dome-Kwabenya (Ghana parliament constituency)|Dome-Kwabenya constituency]] of the [[Ghana Parliament|Ghana parliament]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://library.fes.de/pdf-files/bueros/ghana/03610.pdf |title=Elections 2004. Ghana's Parliamentary and Presidential Elections|accessdate=2011-06-13 |pages=11 |publisher=[[Electoral Commission of Ghana]]| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20110522115353/http://library.fes.de/pdf-files/bueros/ghana/03610.pdf| archivedate= 22 May 2011 <!--DASHBot-->| deadurl= no}}</ref>
==Social Conditions== The town has had numerous issues with the provision of fresh water.The town is divided into three subtowns which are the ashongman estate, Old ashongman and Manna. Almost 70% percent of the roads are bad. The people of Ashongman wants the government to construct roads.<ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=qC9A5UaOAXc Kwabenya - Ashongman Water Supply]. ''[[YouTube]]''.</ref>
