The Maltese nationalist [[Mikiel Anton Vassalli]], a convert to [[Protestantism]], translated the [[Gospel]]s and [[Acts of the Apostles]] into [[Maltese language]]. This was then known as the "[[Kafir]] version". [[Michael Camilleri]] (c.1814–1903), afterwards vicar of [[Lyford, Oxfordshire|Lyford, Berkshire]], revised Vassali's version translated the New Testament and the [[Book of Common Prayer]] into Maltese.

