{{Infobox company | name = Odersun AG | logo = Odersun Logo anthrazit klein.png | logo_size = 250px | caption = | type = [[Public company|Public]] ([[Aktiengesellschaft]]) | traded_as = | fate = | predecessor = | successor = | foundation = {{Start date|2002|11|14|df=y}} | founder = | defunct = {{End date|2012|06|01}} | location_city = [[Frankfurt (Oder)]] | location_country = Germany | locations = | area_served = | key_people = | industry = [[Photovoltaics]] | products = [[CIGS cell]]s, [[thin-film solar cell|thin-film PV technology]] | services = | revenue = | operating_income = | net_income = | assets = | equity = | owner = | num_employees = 320 (2011) | parent = | divisions = | subsid = | homepage = | footnotes = | intl = }}
'''Odersun''' was a German [[photovoltaic]] (PV) company that developed and manufactured [[CIGS cell]]s on a flexible [[copper]] backing, specifically designed for [[building-integrated photovoltaics]]. The insolvent company went into administration on 1 June 2012 and filed for bankruptcy.
Odersun employed more than 320 people in production, research and management in [[Frankfurt (Oder)|Frankfurt an der Oder]], [[Fürstenwalde]] and [[Berlin]], Germany. In cooperation with partner and investor AT&M, the company was setting up a joint venture in Beijing, China.
The company produced its flexible photovoltaic modules according to a proprietary and patented manufacturing process. These [[thin-film solar cell|thin-film modules]] converted sunlight into electricity using a thin layer of a [[copper indium gallium selenide]] (CIGS) [[semiconductor]] which was deposited on copper tape. These were cut, interconnected and built into different forms of modules depending on their application such as [[facade]]s, [[roof]]s, [[canopy (building)|canopies]] or [[louver]]s.
In 2008, the company topped the inaugural Guardian/Library House "CleanTech 100" list, which showcased the then best companies in European clean technology.<ref>[https://www.theguardian.com/environment/2008/sep/18/cleantechnology100.news2 Revealed: Europe's hottest clean technology companies]</ref><ref>[https://www.theguardian.com/environment/table/2008/sep/18/cleantech100top10.cleantechnology100 Top 10: The hottest clean technology companies in Europe]</ref>
